initial statement:
 1091
Your Honor,

I stand before you today, humbly pleading guilty to the offense of careless driving. I fully acknowledge and take responsibility for my actions on the day in question.

On that day, I found myself in a rush to pick up my family members from the airport. In my haste, I made the ill-advised decision to drive aggressively and exceed the speed limit. Additionally, I allowed myself to become distracted by a text message from my cousin, taking my attention away from the road.

These regrettable choices led to a collision with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was harmed in this incident, but I am acutely aware of the potential danger I put myself and others in. I deeply regret my actions and acknowledge the seriousness and potential consequences of my careless driving.

It is important to note that I am 37 years old and have no prior record of criminal behavior. Up until this incident, my driving record has been impeccable. Furthermore, I regularly make contributions to the British Heart Foundation, indicating my commitment to giving back to society and improving the lives of others.

Given these circumstances, I would like to respectfully request that you consider my guilty plea, coupled with my sincere remorse and acknowledgement of the gravity of the offense, as mitigating factors. 

I am committed to learning from this incident and taking necessary steps to prevent it from ever happening again. I am willing to enroll in defensive driving courses to improve my driving skills and ensure the safety of myself and others on the road. Additionally, I am open to participating in community service or any other form of restitution that would allow me to make amends for my actions.

I am truly sorry for the potential harm I caused and the reckless choices I made. I understand the need for accountability and the importance of learning from our mistakes. I assure you that I will do everything within my power to prevent any recurrence of such behavior in the future.

Your Honor, I kindly ask for your leniency and consideration of the mitigating factors present in this case. I am committed to making amends and being a responsible member of society. Thank you for your attention.

Respectfully,

Charlotte Porter
