NEW STATEMENT:

895
Your Honor,

I stand before you today to take full responsibility for my actions and plead guilty to the offense of careless driving that took place on the day in question. I am deeply remorseful for the harm I may have caused and acknowledge the seriousness of my actions.

At the time of the incident, I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members. Unfortunately, I was running late and allowed my impatience to affect my judgment. I regretfully chose to drive aggressively and exceed the speed limit, as well as to respond to a text message from my cousin while driving. These choices were not only irresponsible but also dangerous.

The unfortunate result was that I collided with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was injured in the accident. However, I realize now the potential harm I posed not only to myself but also to innocent individuals on the road. I deeply regret my actions and am fully aware of the consequences they could have had.

As evidence of my sincere remorse, I would like to highlight that I am 37 years old and have an otherwise clean record. I take great pride in maintaining a responsible and law-abiding lifestyle. Additionally, I would like to share that I regularly support the British Heart Foundation through donations, as I believe in giving back to the community.

Your Honor, I humbly request your leniency and understanding as you consider the circumstances surrounding my case. I assure you that I have reflected upon this incident and am committed to personal growth and development. I understand the importance of obeying traffic laws and ensuring the safety of myself and others on the road.

Once again, I express my deepest apologies for my actions and any distress or inconvenience I may have caused. Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely,

Charlotte Porter
